WEBVTT

00:06.923 --> 00:09.843
<i>[soft vocalizing]</i>

00:09.884 --> 00:13.722
<i>* *</i>

00:13.763 --> 00:15.765
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

00:15.807 --> 00:20.979
<i>- Once, long ago,</i>
<i>we lived in the human world.</i>

00:21.021 --> 00:24.566
<i>The Moroi vampires,</i>
<i>who make the rules...</i>

00:24.607 --> 00:26.443
<i>* *</i>

00:26.484 --> 00:28.278
<i>- And the Dhampir Guardians,</i>

00:28.319 --> 00:31.865
<i>sworn to protect</i>
<i>against our enemy,</i>

00:31.906 --> 00:33.658
<i>the Strigoi.</i>

00:33.700 --> 00:36.536
<i>- Undead vampires</i>
<i>who live to kill.</i>

00:36.578 --> 00:39.539
<i>- Now we live</i>
<i>in a world of our own,</i>

00:39.581 --> 00:42.208
<i>one grounded</i>
<i>in elemental magic</i>

00:42.250 --> 00:46.880
<i>and steeped in rules no one's</i>
<i>challenged in centuries...</i>

00:46.921 --> 00:48.214
<i>until now.</i>

00:48.256 --> 00:52.052
<i>* *</i>

00:52.093 --> 00:56.473
<i>- The spark of revolution</i>
<i>can come from anywhere.</i>

00:56.514 --> 00:58.725
<i>Even two unlikely friends.</i>

01:00.769 --> 01:04.022
<i>- And one night</i>
<i>that changed everything.</i>

01:04.064 --> 01:06.775
<i>* *</i>

01:06.816 --> 01:11.363
<i>[soft vocalizing]</i>

01:11.404 --> 01:14.282
<i>[electronic orchestral music]</i>

01:14.324 --> 01:21.373
<i>* *</i>

01:36.262 --> 01:39.057
- [sighs]
I look like a fucking macaroon.

01:39.099 --> 01:40.725
<i>* *</i>

01:40.767 --> 01:44.062
- And now you look
like a princess.

01:44.104 --> 01:46.564
<i>* *</i>

01:46.606 --> 01:49.317
[gasps]
- Ooh, ooh.

01:49.359 --> 01:51.403
Ugh, how do you
even wear this thing?

01:51.444 --> 01:53.279
I just lost a hundred strands.

01:53.321 --> 01:55.323
- Heavy is the head,
thin is the hair.

01:56.825 --> 01:59.160
Rose, if anyone looks
like a macaroon, it's me.

01:59.202 --> 02:00.286
You look beautiful.

02:00.328 --> 02:02.288
- We look beautiful, Lissa,

02:02.330 --> 02:03.832
head to toe.

02:05.083 --> 02:06.292
Let's party.

02:07.419 --> 02:09.796
<i>- To all citizens</i>
<i>of the Dominion,</i>

02:09.838 --> 02:13.049
<i>on this,</i>
<i>the eve of my 200th birthday</i>

02:13.091 --> 02:16.386
<i>and my last as your queen,</i>
<i>I thank you.</i>

02:16.428 --> 02:18.763
<i>You have traveled</i>
<i>far and wide,</i>

02:18.805 --> 02:21.599
<i>leaving the safety</i>
<i>of your provinces</i>

02:21.641 --> 02:25.186
<i>to come to the celebration</i>
<i>here at St. Vladimir's.</i>

02:25.228 --> 02:29.524
<i>We all know the dangers</i>
<i>that lurk outside our gates.</i>

02:29.566 --> 02:33.862
<i>Our Strigoi enemy is strong,</i>
<i>but we are stronger.</i>

02:33.903 --> 02:38.241
<i>And under the protection</i>
<i>of our Dhampir Guardians,</i>

02:38.283 --> 02:40.410
<i>we are safe.</i>

02:40.452 --> 02:44.205
<i>So let us have</i>
<i>one last festivity together,</i>

02:44.247 --> 02:47.667
<i>because after nearly</i>
<i>two centuries as your queen,</i>

02:47.709 --> 02:51.212
<i>the one thing</i>
<i>I assure you I've learned</i>

02:51.254 --> 02:55.175
<i>is how to throw</i>
<i>one hell of a party.</i>

02:55.216 --> 02:58.011
<i>[upbeat electronic music]</i>

02:58.053 --> 03:01.598
<i>* *</i>

03:01.639 --> 03:03.391
- [gasps]

03:03.433 --> 03:07.729
<i>* *</i>

03:07.771 --> 03:09.397
- Victor Dashkov.

03:11.566 --> 03:15.653
My daughters,
Sonya Karp, Mia Karp.

03:15.695 --> 03:19.032
- One Royal Moroi, one non.

03:19.074 --> 03:20.867
And the third?
- Mia.

03:20.909 --> 03:22.786
- The Guardians make us suffer
through this every time.

03:22.827 --> 03:25.121
- It's security protocol.
- It's humiliating.

03:25.163 --> 03:26.623
How do they not know who I am?

03:26.664 --> 03:29.084
- Mia, darling.
Be a sport.

03:29.125 --> 03:34.130
<i>* *</i>

03:34.172 --> 03:36.466
- Non-Royal.

03:36.508 --> 03:38.718
- Not for long.

03:38.760 --> 03:42.138
<i>- * Move now,</i>
<i>this is natural *</i>

03:42.180 --> 03:45.558
<i>* And I need your touch *</i>

03:45.600 --> 03:48.436
<i>* Oh, come the blinding sun *</i>

03:48.478 --> 03:50.772
<i>* I already fled the scene *</i>

03:50.814 --> 03:55.193
<i>* I'm already gone,</i>
<i>there's so much more to see *</i>

03:55.235 --> 03:56.569
<i>* I can feel the night *</i>

03:56.611 --> 03:57.737
- Rose.
- Hmm?

03:57.779 --> 04:00.365
- Behave.
- Always, Alberta.

04:00.407 --> 04:01.825
- Don't encourage her.

04:01.866 --> 04:03.910
- She's a guest
of a Moroi princess.

04:03.952 --> 04:05.412
Let her have some fun.

04:05.453 --> 04:07.914
- Guardians aren't here
to have fun.

04:07.956 --> 04:14.879
<i>* *</i>

04:19.467 --> 04:21.302
- Once my family
greets the Queen,

04:21.344 --> 04:22.929
we can have some fun.

04:24.764 --> 04:26.975
Nice.
- Excuse you.

04:27.017 --> 04:29.728
<i>* *</i>

04:29.769 --> 04:31.229
- What are
the Dragomirs thinking,

04:31.271 --> 04:33.773
letting Lissa invite that girl
everywhere she goes?

04:33.815 --> 04:37.318
A Guardian's place
is at the gates.

04:37.360 --> 04:39.654
<i>- * I'ma make my own way *</i>

04:39.696 --> 04:42.824
<i>[dramatic orchestral music]</i>

04:42.866 --> 04:49.664
<i>* *</i>

04:49.706 --> 04:53.418
- The Dragomirs, Your Majesty.
- [scoffs]

04:53.460 --> 04:57.589
Clarence would introduce
his father to his mother.

04:57.630 --> 05:00.258
How are
my delightful Dragomirs?

05:00.300 --> 05:02.969
- Happy Birthday, Fair Lady.
You don't look a day over 80.

05:03.011 --> 05:07.098
- Andre, my dear,
you cheeky rascal.

05:07.140 --> 05:10.018
And a dreadful liar.

05:10.060 --> 05:13.021
- Happy birthday from me
as well, Your Majesty.

05:13.063 --> 05:15.398
- Princess Vasilissa,

05:15.440 --> 05:17.776
angel to your brother
Andre's devil.

05:17.817 --> 05:19.736
- He is shameless,
Your Majesty.

05:19.778 --> 05:21.196
How should he be punished?

05:21.237 --> 05:24.949
- Being King of the Dominion
will be punishment enough.

05:24.991 --> 05:31.748
<i>* *</i>

05:33.375 --> 05:35.126
Oh, surely,
he'll find something

05:35.168 --> 05:37.253
to cheer him once he's king.

05:37.295 --> 05:38.630
- Now, Your Majesty,

05:38.672 --> 05:40.674
you know there'll have
to be an actual election.

05:40.715 --> 05:43.718
- Ah, a mere formality.

05:43.760 --> 05:47.013
Who would deny me
my pick of successor?

05:47.055 --> 05:51.184
If I say Andre will be king,
then so it shall be.

05:51.226 --> 05:55.355
<i>* *</i>

05:55.397 --> 05:58.024
[cheers and applause]

05:58.066 --> 06:00.610
- Looks like
Mia lost her prince.

06:00.652 --> 06:02.195
- I'm amazed she let him
out of her sight

06:02.237 --> 06:03.780
long enough to lose him.

06:03.822 --> 06:06.658
- [chuckles]
- Where is Andre?

06:06.700 --> 06:10.036
[both moaning]

06:10.078 --> 06:12.372
crowd: * Happy birthday,
dear... *

06:12.414 --> 06:14.499
- Shit, I gotta go.
- Uh-uh.

06:14.541 --> 06:17.877
[both moaning]

06:20.755 --> 06:23.258
- Never leave a girl undone,
Andre,

06:23.299 --> 06:25.093
not even for the Queen.

06:25.135 --> 06:29.264
[distant singing continues]

06:29.305 --> 06:30.640
- It's a pleasure
to meet you...

06:30.682 --> 06:33.018
- Tatiana.
- Tatiana.

06:37.272 --> 06:40.233
<i>[ominous music]</i>

06:40.275 --> 06:41.568
<i>* *</i>

06:41.609 --> 06:43.945
[twig snaps]

06:43.987 --> 06:50.952
<i>* *</i>

06:58.501 --> 07:02.005
[ravens crowing]

07:02.047 --> 07:05.550
<i>* *</i>

07:05.592 --> 07:07.427
- [growls]

07:07.469 --> 07:09.637
- [grunts]
- Strigoi!

07:09.679 --> 07:11.056
<i>- * Survival of the fittest,</i>
<i>yeah *</i>

07:11.097 --> 07:13.099
<i>* But all up in my business *</i>

07:13.141 --> 07:15.018
<i>* Caught up in calm,</i>
<i>I know you gotta *</i>

07:15.060 --> 07:16.936
<i>* Run before you get it,</i>
<i>yeah *</i>

07:16.978 --> 07:18.730
<i>* One, I love a party *</i>

07:18.772 --> 07:20.523
<i>* Love the way you haunt me *</i>

07:20.565 --> 07:22.067
<i>* Put me where you want me *</i>

07:22.108 --> 07:24.652
<i>* Just one sip,</i>
<i>you won't be sorry *</i>

07:24.694 --> 07:28.073
<i>- Strigoi at the wards.</i>
<i>Guardian support, stat.</i>

07:28.114 --> 07:30.075
<i>- * Love the way</i>
<i>you haunt me *</i>

07:30.116 --> 07:31.284
<i>* Right there</i>
<i>where you want me *</i>

07:31.326 --> 07:34.037
[all grunting]

07:34.079 --> 07:37.374
<i>* *</i>

07:37.415 --> 07:41.127
<i>* Right there</i>
<i>where you want me, ay, ay *</i>

07:41.169 --> 07:46.925
<i>* *</i>

07:46.966 --> 07:50.512
<i>* Pour me whiskey soda,</i>
<i>I cannot be sober *</i>

07:50.553 --> 07:54.391
<i>* One shot and I'm up,</i>
<i>two shots and it's over *</i>

07:54.432 --> 07:56.976
<i>* Show me how you like it *</i>

07:57.018 --> 07:58.687
- [screams]

07:58.728 --> 07:59.771
<i>- * Show me</i>
<i>what you came with *</i>

07:59.813 --> 08:02.190
<i>* I'ma show you guidance *</i>

08:02.232 --> 08:03.566
- [snarls]

08:03.608 --> 08:05.527
<i>- * Bodies on top of bodies *</i>

08:05.568 --> 08:07.028
<i>* Love the way you haunt me *</i>

08:07.070 --> 08:09.114
<i>- Strigoi neutralized.</i>
<i>Back to positions.</i>

08:09.155 --> 08:11.324
<i>* *</i>

08:11.366 --> 08:14.703
<i>- * Love the way you haunt me,</i>
<i>ay, ay, ay *</i>

08:14.744 --> 08:16.496
<i>* Just one sip,</i>
<i>you won't be sorry *</i>

08:16.538 --> 08:18.665
<i>* Ay, ay, ay *</i>

08:18.707 --> 08:23.294
<i>* *</i>

08:23.336 --> 08:24.671
<i>* Run up, run up *</i>

08:24.713 --> 08:26.840
<i>* *</i>

08:26.881 --> 08:28.591
<i>* Run up, run up *</i>

08:28.633 --> 08:30.885
<i>* *</i>

08:30.927 --> 08:33.388
<i>* Run up, run up *</i>

08:33.430 --> 08:35.640
[laughter]

08:35.682 --> 08:37.225
- You know,
I'm pretty sure Andre danced

08:37.267 --> 08:39.477
with every single girl
at that party.

08:39.519 --> 08:40.979
- Poor Mia.

08:41.021 --> 08:42.689
- "Poor Mia" will get
the only thing

08:42.731 --> 08:45.442
she really wants once we marry.

08:45.483 --> 08:48.653
Royal status.
[laughter]

08:48.695 --> 08:51.531
- My son,
the next King of the Dominion.

08:51.573 --> 08:54.200
- I hate to admit it,
but you will make a great king.

08:54.242 --> 08:57.162
- If I can get the factions
to remember we're not enemies,

08:57.203 --> 08:59.914
it'll go a long way
towards peace in the Dominion.

08:59.956 --> 09:02.292
You know, Rose, I get my pick
of Guardian once I'm king.

09:02.334 --> 09:03.793
- Sorry, once I graduate,

09:03.835 --> 09:06.046
Lissa and I will be too busy
exploring the world.

09:06.087 --> 09:09.299
- Yeah, and everyone knows
I want Rose to be my Guardian.

09:09.341 --> 09:10.800
I'm not budging on that.

09:10.842 --> 09:12.218
- What we want
and what we must do

09:12.260 --> 09:13.720
can be
two very different things.

09:13.762 --> 09:16.181
- Maybe, Your Almost Majesty.

09:16.222 --> 09:17.932
But not tonight.

09:17.974 --> 09:20.352
A toast

09:20.393 --> 09:22.562
to having everything I want.

09:22.604 --> 09:23.730
A know-it-all big brother...

09:23.772 --> 09:24.981
[both hiss]

09:25.023 --> 09:28.026
- Kids.
[laughter]

09:28.068 --> 09:29.861
- The most supportive parents
either one of us

09:29.903 --> 09:32.906
could ever hope for,

09:32.947 --> 09:36.284
and Rose,
my best friend for life.

09:36.326 --> 09:38.203
[screaming]

09:38.244 --> 09:40.580
[glass shattering]

09:40.622 --> 09:43.541
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

09:43.583 --> 09:50.674
<i>* *</i>

09:57.555 --> 10:00.475
<i>[dramatic vocalizing]</i>

10:00.517 --> 10:07.649
<i>* *</i>

10:30.213 --> 10:33.174
<i>[somber music]</i>

10:33.216 --> 10:40.140
<i>* *</i>

10:48.189 --> 10:49.816
I don't know
how to say goodbye.

10:49.858 --> 10:52.068
<i>* *</i>

10:52.110 --> 10:54.487
I don't know how any of us
are supposed to go on

10:54.529 --> 10:55.822
without you.

10:55.864 --> 10:59.451
<i>* *</i>

10:59.492 --> 11:02.495
Mom.

11:02.537 --> 11:06.207
Dad.

11:06.249 --> 11:07.500
Andre.

11:07.542 --> 11:10.462
<i>* *</i>

11:10.503 --> 11:13.256
I will love you forever.

11:13.298 --> 11:18.219
<i>* *</i>

11:20.722 --> 11:22.932
I'm ready to go back.

11:22.974 --> 11:24.851
- Are you sure?

11:27.187 --> 11:29.272
- It's time.

11:29.314 --> 11:32.233
<i>[exciting music]</i>

11:32.275 --> 11:39.240
<i>* *</i>

12:02.263 --> 12:03.807
- [grunts]

12:03.848 --> 12:10.980
<i>* *</i>

12:25.495 --> 12:26.746
- Lissa.

12:26.788 --> 12:27.956
- Stop.

12:34.921 --> 12:37.632
- It's all right.
Rose won't harm Lissa.

12:37.674 --> 12:39.300
- She has something.

12:39.342 --> 12:40.969
Show me.

12:42.303 --> 12:45.974
- It's a super dangerous
welcome home gift.

12:47.392 --> 12:50.854
- I love it.
I mean, I'm not 12, but--

12:50.895 --> 12:52.647
- Shut up.
It's fucking adorable.

12:52.689 --> 12:55.316
- [laughs]

12:56.860 --> 12:58.445
[indistinct chatter]

12:58.486 --> 12:59.946
- Who was that guy?

12:59.988 --> 13:03.450
- That was Dimitri,
my new Guardian.

13:03.491 --> 13:05.660
- Not for long.
- No, I know. Don't worry.

13:05.702 --> 13:08.371
You're still gonna be assigned
to me after we graduate.

13:08.413 --> 13:09.706
- Will I?

13:09.748 --> 13:12.167
Maybe when Andre was going
to be king, but now--

13:12.208 --> 13:14.669
- But no one can say no
to me right now.

13:14.711 --> 13:17.297
Not after--

13:17.339 --> 13:20.884
we're just gonna have
to ride it out for a while.

13:20.925 --> 13:22.302
- Right.

13:22.344 --> 13:24.095
We're not gonna let Dimitri
or anything else

13:24.137 --> 13:27.057
get in our way
of our plans for the future.

13:27.098 --> 13:30.185
- He is good-looking, though.
- I didn't notice.

13:40.070 --> 13:43.031
<i>[tender music]</i>

13:43.073 --> 13:47.494
<i>* *</i>

13:47.535 --> 13:49.037
What's this for?

13:49.079 --> 13:52.999
- I'm just...really,

13:53.041 --> 13:55.043
really happy to see you.

13:55.085 --> 14:00.340
<i>* *</i>

14:00.382 --> 14:02.258
- Will Rose Hathaway
be a problem?

14:02.300 --> 14:03.843
- Rose is always a problem.

14:03.885 --> 14:05.595
She's one of our best
Guardian Novices,

14:05.637 --> 14:07.681
but she's a handful.

14:07.722 --> 14:09.808
- The girls have been friends
their entire lives.

14:09.849 --> 14:13.269
I mean, we've spoiled them.
Let them break all the rules.

14:13.311 --> 14:15.605
Even let them be roommates
in the Moroi dorms.

14:15.647 --> 14:17.107
Is it any surprise

14:17.148 --> 14:18.650
Rose would have
certain expectations?

14:18.692 --> 14:20.568
- A Guardian's duty is
to do as they're told.

14:20.610 --> 14:24.155
- With all due respect,
I'm not a nanny.

14:24.197 --> 14:26.825
My job is protection.

14:26.866 --> 14:30.161
- A word that can take
many forms.

14:30.203 --> 14:33.123
<i>[tense music]</i>

14:33.164 --> 14:36.751
<i>* *</i>

14:36.793 --> 14:39.087
- [gasping]

14:41.297 --> 14:43.591
[sighs]

14:45.760 --> 14:49.055
- Oh, that's nice.

14:49.097 --> 14:55.603
<i>* *</i>

14:55.645 --> 14:57.397
- Whoa.

14:57.439 --> 15:00.859
Look who's back from the dead.

15:00.900 --> 15:02.360
Too soon.

15:02.402 --> 15:03.695
- It's nice to see you too,
Jesse.

15:03.737 --> 15:05.488
- So a little birdie told me

15:05.530 --> 15:09.034
you'll be head
of the Dragomir family now.

15:09.075 --> 15:12.078
I hope my father
can count on your vote.

15:12.120 --> 15:14.372
- I don't know, Jesse.

15:14.414 --> 15:17.083
Honestly, the political stuff
was Andre's thing, not mine.

15:17.125 --> 15:19.002
- [scoffs]

15:19.044 --> 15:24.549
<i>* *</i>

15:24.591 --> 15:27.761
- You know,
we Feeders hear a lot.

15:27.802 --> 15:30.597
You're smart to stay out of it.

15:30.638 --> 15:34.559
The politics in this place
have gotten really ugly.

15:35.977 --> 15:37.062
Be careful.

15:37.103 --> 15:41.524
<i>* *</i>

15:41.566 --> 15:45.070
- It's dangerous to wait
too long, Your Majesty.

15:45.111 --> 15:47.072
We need strong leadership now.

15:47.113 --> 15:49.949
I assume you'll name
your successor soon.

15:49.991 --> 15:51.326
I have some thoughts.

15:51.368 --> 15:54.996
- And I have a date
with an old friend.

15:55.038 --> 15:56.664
You're excused, Marie.

16:00.835 --> 16:02.420
- Your Majesty.

16:09.260 --> 16:11.346
- You see what I'm up against?

16:11.388 --> 16:13.807
Instead of mourning the man
who could unite them,

16:13.848 --> 16:17.143
these idiots are all scrambling
for the crown.

16:17.185 --> 16:19.646
- Hmm.
- Enough.

16:19.688 --> 16:21.398
There's work to be done.

16:21.439 --> 16:23.483
You must prepare Lissa
for her new role

16:23.525 --> 16:25.235
as head of the Dragomir family.

16:25.276 --> 16:26.986
- It won't be easy for her.

16:27.028 --> 16:29.614
You know, she was planning
to apply for a dispensation

16:29.656 --> 16:31.157
to study art abroad.

16:31.199 --> 16:33.076
- Those dreams are done.

16:33.118 --> 16:34.661
Lissa must finish her schooling

16:34.703 --> 16:37.706
and take her rightful place
in the Royal Court.

16:37.747 --> 16:38.748
- And Rose?

16:38.790 --> 16:40.792
- When she finishes
her training,

16:40.834 --> 16:44.546
we'll find her a placement
in one of the other provinces.

16:44.587 --> 16:47.549
- She won't like that.
- Moroi come first.

16:47.590 --> 16:50.885
Rose knows that.
She'll do her duty.

16:50.927 --> 16:54.055
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

17:00.020 --> 17:02.939
<i>[soft music]</i>

17:02.981 --> 17:10.113
<i>* *</i>

17:14.701 --> 17:17.495
- Might help if we flicked on
an actual light, right?

17:17.537 --> 17:20.165
- That would damage the paper.
It's a thousand years old.

17:20.206 --> 17:23.084
- Oh, of course.

17:23.126 --> 17:25.670
Not sure it would help anyway.

17:25.712 --> 17:27.380
- You only need to recite

17:27.422 --> 17:29.466
this small passage
for the consecration.

17:29.507 --> 17:30.925
- Recite?

17:30.967 --> 17:33.762
I need to recite Old Moroi
in front of people, tonight?

17:33.803 --> 17:35.972
- Any new head of a family
must be blessed

17:36.014 --> 17:38.266
in the presence
of all the others.

17:38.308 --> 17:41.478
Sorry, it's tradition.

17:51.446 --> 17:53.323
- That's a beautiful yellow
you're wearing.

17:56.659 --> 18:00.121
- Thank you, Sonya.
I really like it too.

18:07.295 --> 18:10.423
[speaking Old Moroi]

18:12.634 --> 18:15.887
[wind whooshing]

18:15.929 --> 18:22.811
<i>* *</i>

18:27.941 --> 18:30.819
All right, who's there?

18:30.860 --> 18:34.406
<i>* *</i>

18:34.447 --> 18:36.950
- Thought you could use
some light.

18:36.991 --> 18:39.911
<i>* *</i>

18:39.953 --> 18:42.247
- And you are?
- New.

18:42.288 --> 18:45.709
<i>* *</i>

18:45.750 --> 18:49.045
I'm Christian Ozera.

18:49.087 --> 18:50.338
- Oh.

18:50.380 --> 18:52.966
- And just to get it
out of the way, no,

18:53.008 --> 18:55.760
I don't know why my parents
chose the ultimate sin

18:55.802 --> 18:57.137
and turned Strigoi.

18:57.178 --> 19:01.016
And since they're dead,
can't ask them.

19:01.057 --> 19:04.185
- So you, what, just hang
around old church archives

19:04.227 --> 19:05.603
waiting for girls
to need a light?

19:05.645 --> 19:09.899
- Or might just have
some questions

19:09.941 --> 19:11.651
about where we go after we die.

19:11.693 --> 19:14.612
<i>* *</i>

19:14.654 --> 19:16.573
- I'm sorry about your parents.

19:18.742 --> 19:19.951
- I'm sorry about yours.

19:19.993 --> 19:23.455
<i>* *</i>

19:23.496 --> 19:25.665
- So, um--
[clears throat]

19:25.707 --> 19:27.625
Do you actually read
this stuff?

19:27.667 --> 19:30.962
- Well, I'm not exactly on top
of anyone's invite list.

19:31.004 --> 19:35.133
I got time. Lots of time.

19:35.175 --> 19:37.886
And you'd be surprised
by the secrets

19:37.927 --> 19:40.513
these dusty records hold.

19:40.555 --> 19:45.143
Plus, Old Moroi really is
kind of...

19:45.185 --> 19:46.644
beautiful.

19:46.686 --> 19:50.023
<i>* *</i>

19:50.065 --> 19:52.984
- I don't think I can do this.

19:53.026 --> 19:54.861
- Say it with me.

19:54.903 --> 19:56.863
- Okay.
- Yeah.

19:56.905 --> 19:59.783
[both speaking Old Moroi]

20:05.622 --> 20:06.456
- Yeah.

20:06.498 --> 20:09.584
[both speaking Old Moroi]

20:18.301 --> 20:25.392
<i>* *</i>

20:38.738 --> 20:40.657
- You know
we have wards around the gates

20:40.699 --> 20:42.492
to keep us safe from Strigoi.

20:42.534 --> 20:45.412
Lissa doesn't need 24/7 detail.

20:45.453 --> 20:49.124
- Lissa's still at the church.
Royals only.

20:49.165 --> 20:50.792
- So you're just...

20:50.834 --> 20:53.253
having a staring contest
with the air?

20:53.294 --> 20:55.046
- You've studied
perimeter control.

20:55.088 --> 20:57.132
- Yes. Got an A.

20:57.173 --> 20:59.509
- What's around this perimeter?

20:59.551 --> 21:03.263
Don't look.
Just tell me.

21:03.304 --> 21:05.849
- Street clear. Gate secured.

21:05.890 --> 21:07.892
Rooftop empty.
Turrets contained.

21:07.934 --> 21:09.102
- How do you know?

21:09.144 --> 21:10.228
- I've trained for years

21:10.270 --> 21:11.896
to know every inch
of this place.

21:11.938 --> 21:12.939
- Exactly.

21:12.981 --> 21:14.691
You're able to operate
on instinct

21:14.733 --> 21:15.984
because you're
intimately familiar

21:16.026 --> 21:17.360
with your surroundings.

21:17.402 --> 21:19.446
But I'm new here.

21:19.487 --> 21:22.115
Lots to learn in a little time.

21:23.116 --> 21:25.577
So I suppose you could say
I'm having a staring contest

21:25.618 --> 21:28.580
with the street, the gates,

21:28.621 --> 21:31.875
the rooftops, and the turrets.

21:33.626 --> 21:35.670
- You're kind of
a Guardian nerd, aren't you?

21:38.757 --> 21:42.719
It's cool.
Do your thing, perimeter man.

21:42.761 --> 21:44.763
But just know
I plan on taking your job

21:44.804 --> 21:47.098
when I graduate.

21:47.140 --> 21:48.767
- I agree.

21:48.808 --> 21:50.685
Lissa would be
in perfectly good hands

21:50.727 --> 21:53.438
with the best Guardian
at St. Vladimir's Academy.

21:53.480 --> 21:54.606
- Thank you.

21:54.647 --> 21:57.442
- Although that may be hard,

21:57.484 --> 21:58.777
given your ranking.

21:58.818 --> 22:02.447
- I'm number one.
I'm always number one.

22:02.489 --> 22:04.574
- Then perhaps...
you're not as good

22:04.616 --> 22:06.659
at perimeter control
as you think.

22:12.957 --> 22:14.459
- What the fuck?

22:14.501 --> 22:17.420
<i>[tense music]</i>

22:17.462 --> 22:19.464
<i>* *</i>

22:19.506 --> 22:22.967
Hey! How am I fifth?

22:23.009 --> 22:25.387
- You missed class.
It's an automatic ten demerits.

22:25.428 --> 22:27.555
It's very tight, the top five.

22:27.597 --> 22:29.933
- I missed class to welcome
Lissa back to school.

22:29.974 --> 22:32.018
- Find me a Strigoi
who will accept that excuse,

22:32.060 --> 22:33.853
and we'll talk.

22:33.895 --> 22:40.652
<i>* *</i>

22:40.694 --> 22:43.321
- Game on, Hathaway.

22:43.363 --> 22:46.241
- Don't get comfortable, Mace.

22:46.282 --> 22:49.035
- Positions!

22:49.077 --> 22:50.870
Go!
[all shout]

22:50.912 --> 22:56.418
<i>* *</i>

22:56.459 --> 22:59.587
[all shouting]

22:59.629 --> 23:02.757
[bell tolling]

23:17.689 --> 23:20.859
<i>[soft pop music]</i>

23:20.900 --> 23:27.824
<i>* *</i>

23:30.577 --> 23:33.246
<i>- * Look up to the stars *</i>

23:33.288 --> 23:37.584
<i>* *</i>

23:37.625 --> 23:41.463
<i>* High up in the sky *</i>

23:41.504 --> 23:48.511
<i>* *</i>

23:55.977 --> 23:57.771
- [clears throat]

24:01.691 --> 24:06.488
<i>- * Nothing</i>
<i>but the fading light *</i>

24:06.529 --> 24:08.573
<i>* *</i>

24:08.615 --> 24:13.703
<i>* Nothing</i>
<i>but the fading light *</i>

24:13.745 --> 24:16.790
- [speaking Old Moroi]

24:21.628 --> 24:26.007
<i>- * Look up to the stars *</i>

24:45.485 --> 24:48.488
- It's Friday.
It's Challenge Day.

24:48.530 --> 24:52.158
She wants to boost her ranking.

24:52.200 --> 24:53.785
- Come on, already?

24:53.827 --> 24:55.745
I've only gotten to be
number one for, like, a day.

24:55.787 --> 24:57.414
- I'm more comfortable on top.

24:57.455 --> 24:59.124
- [chuckles]
Don't I know it.

25:01.543 --> 25:03.670
[whistle blows]

25:03.712 --> 25:06.172
[all cheering]

25:06.214 --> 25:09.175
[both grunting]

25:09.217 --> 25:12.262
<i>[tense music]</i>

25:12.303 --> 25:19.185
<i>* *</i>

25:22.689 --> 25:24.983
- Come on.
She's got it, she's got it.

25:25.025 --> 25:27.986
[all cheering]

25:28.028 --> 25:34.993
<i>* *</i>

25:37.162 --> 25:39.622
- [laughs]
He's not coming back.

25:39.664 --> 25:46.629
<i>* *</i>

25:46.671 --> 25:49.549
[both grunting]

25:52.344 --> 25:54.012
[buzzer blares]

25:54.054 --> 25:55.555
[all cheering]

25:55.597 --> 25:57.098
- A fucking draw?

25:57.140 --> 25:59.726
- Round two, weapons.

25:59.768 --> 26:02.103
- Nice!
There it is!

26:02.145 --> 26:03.646
[cheering]

26:03.688 --> 26:06.608
[light string music playing]

26:06.649 --> 26:08.777
* *

26:08.818 --> 26:11.905
- I'm not sure
you should be here.

26:11.946 --> 26:15.533
* *

26:15.575 --> 26:18.661
- I'm a Royal.
Can't keep me out.

26:18.703 --> 26:24.709
* *

26:24.751 --> 26:27.712
<i>[soft music]</i>

26:27.754 --> 26:34.886
<i>* *</i>

26:45.647 --> 26:47.273
- I'm surprised
to see you here.

26:47.315 --> 26:48.692
- Yeah, it's been a while

26:48.733 --> 26:50.860
since I've been
to one of these things.

26:50.902 --> 26:53.905
People generally aren't
very, um...

26:53.947 --> 26:55.782
excited to see my face.

26:55.824 --> 26:57.242
- So why did you come?

26:57.283 --> 26:58.827
- To see if you needed
an Old Moroi tutor.

26:58.868 --> 27:00.036
Your heart's in it,

27:00.078 --> 27:02.455
but your pronunciation
is terrible.

27:02.497 --> 27:05.792
- [laughs]

27:05.834 --> 27:08.378
- The Queen is looking for you.

27:08.420 --> 27:15.385
<i>* *</i>

27:15.427 --> 27:18.388
<i>[intense music]</i>

27:18.430 --> 27:24.060
<i>* *</i>

27:24.102 --> 27:25.395
- I'm impressed.

27:25.437 --> 27:26.646
Rose is half Mason's size,

27:26.688 --> 27:28.231
but she's using it
as an advantage.

27:28.273 --> 27:29.566
- Trust me,

27:29.607 --> 27:31.151
she'll do something
to fuck it up.

27:31.192 --> 27:33.737
- Christian Ozera
is a nonstarter.

27:33.778 --> 27:35.739
His parents chose
to turn Strigoi.

27:35.780 --> 27:38.533
- That's not his fault.
- It's a mortal sin.

27:38.575 --> 27:40.660
The last thing you need
is the church against you.

27:40.702 --> 27:42.495
Now, we need
to discuss your schedule.

27:42.537 --> 27:44.289
The other heads of families
will be inviting you

27:44.330 --> 27:46.041
to a series
of less formal events,

27:46.082 --> 27:48.251
although still mandatory,
starting tomorrow.

27:48.293 --> 27:50.545
- I get it--there has to be
an official head of family.

27:50.587 --> 27:53.423
But in just a few months,
Rose and I are out of here.

27:53.465 --> 27:56.259
Why waste your time teaching me
something I'm never gonna use?

27:56.301 --> 27:57.719
- Unfortunately, kiddo,

27:57.761 --> 27:59.971
Andre's death changes
everything for you,

28:00.013 --> 28:02.599
including your plans
for your future.

28:02.640 --> 28:04.851
What we want
and what we must do

28:04.893 --> 28:06.978
are often miles apart.

28:07.020 --> 28:09.147
- What we want
and what we must do

28:09.189 --> 28:11.232
can be
two very different things.

28:11.274 --> 28:14.152
[glass shattering]

28:16.529 --> 28:19.240
- [breathing heavily]

28:20.492 --> 28:22.869
[gasping]

28:22.911 --> 28:26.915
<i>* *</i>

28:26.956 --> 28:28.583
<i>- Lissa, what's wrong?</i>

28:28.625 --> 28:29.709
- [gasps]

28:29.751 --> 28:31.753
[both grunting]

28:31.795 --> 28:34.714
[buzzer blares]

28:48.770 --> 28:50.897
- [laughs]
Here you go.

28:50.939 --> 28:53.316
Some for you and you.

28:53.358 --> 28:56.277
<i>[soft music]</i>

28:56.319 --> 29:03.118
<i>* *</i>

29:03.159 --> 29:05.620
- Anything interesting
out there?

29:05.662 --> 29:08.665
- Just Sonya, the bird lady.

29:08.707 --> 29:11.418
- Be gentle on your sister.
- I am.

29:11.459 --> 29:12.961
Sometimes.

29:13.003 --> 29:14.587
I just don't understand
why she has to be

29:14.629 --> 29:16.256
so weird all the time.

29:16.297 --> 29:19.175
- Sweetie, you need
to give that back to Lissa.

29:21.469 --> 29:23.888
- I do not.

29:23.930 --> 29:25.807
And anyway, I'm wearing it
to the reception tomorrow.

29:25.849 --> 29:27.851
- I'm sorry, Mia.
It's Royals only.

29:27.892 --> 29:31.312
The queen was very insistent.
- So that's it?

29:31.354 --> 29:33.440
One minute,
I'm the future king's fiancÃ©e,

29:33.481 --> 29:36.484
and the next, I'm invisible?

29:36.526 --> 29:37.944
I'm keeping the necklace.

29:37.986 --> 29:39.821
- It's a Dragomir
family heirloom.

29:39.863 --> 29:41.239
- And a Dragomir gave it to me.

29:41.281 --> 29:43.491
- And with Andre dead,
you can't keep it.

29:43.533 --> 29:46.494
<i>[tense music]</i>

29:46.536 --> 29:48.663
- I was so close.

29:48.705 --> 29:50.040
Maybe he didn't love me,

29:50.081 --> 29:51.416
and I didn't love him
in that way,

29:51.458 --> 29:53.209
but we were good together.

29:55.170 --> 29:57.047
And I would have made
a great queen.

29:59.883 --> 30:02.302
- There's a lot you can do

30:02.344 --> 30:05.638
without ever sitting
on a throne.

30:05.680 --> 30:09.225
Having the ear of the Queen
can be just as powerful.

30:11.061 --> 30:15.690
And the Queen has big plans
for Lissa.

30:15.732 --> 30:19.069
- Lissa's a twit.
- [chuckles]

30:19.110 --> 30:21.696
- What is up with Sonya
and those fucking birds?

30:21.738 --> 30:26.326
<i>* *</i>

30:26.368 --> 30:29.245
- [breathing heavily]

30:38.421 --> 30:41.132
[door clicks]

30:46.888 --> 30:48.515
- Lissa.
- [gasps]

30:48.556 --> 30:50.058
- What are you doing?

30:50.100 --> 30:52.852
- I just feel like
everything's out of control.

30:52.894 --> 30:56.398
We were all just here together,
and then--

30:56.439 --> 30:59.526
and then there's an accident
that I can barely remember.

30:59.567 --> 31:01.361
And the only thing I know

31:01.403 --> 31:04.531
is that Andre should be here,
not me.

31:04.572 --> 31:08.243
- Shh, shh, shh.
That's just the grief talking.

31:08.284 --> 31:10.620
- [sobbing]

31:10.662 --> 31:13.039
- Shh, it's okay.

31:13.081 --> 31:16.710
<i>[soft music]</i>

31:16.751 --> 31:20.630
But if we're going to sunbathe,

31:20.672 --> 31:22.757
I know where I want to be.

31:22.799 --> 31:27.762
<i>* *</i>

31:27.804 --> 31:31.307
<i>- * Ooh, ooh *</i>

31:31.349 --> 31:36.730
<i>* *</i>

31:36.771 --> 31:40.316
<i>* Ooh, ooh *</i>

31:40.358 --> 31:41.985
<i>* *</i>

31:42.027 --> 31:44.863
- This is the first place
your family took me.

31:44.904 --> 31:49.242
- I remember.
Right after I met you.

31:49.284 --> 31:51.703
Standing all alone
on Family Day.

31:51.745 --> 31:54.748
- You ran straight up to me.
- [laughs tearfully]

31:54.789 --> 31:56.207
- Your clothes were so clean,

31:56.249 --> 31:58.543
I was afraid your parents
wouldn't let you play with me.

31:58.585 --> 32:01.338
[laughing]

32:01.379 --> 32:04.007
I didn't know
what a family was until then.

32:04.049 --> 32:07.177
[breathes deeply]

32:09.220 --> 32:12.098
- You keep asking me
if I'm gonna be okay.

32:14.017 --> 32:15.810
Are you?

32:15.852 --> 32:20.899
<i>* *</i>

32:20.940 --> 32:25.153
- They were everything
a family should be.

32:25.195 --> 32:28.448
Your mum hugged me
every time I saw her,

32:28.490 --> 32:30.325
hello and goodbye.

32:30.367 --> 32:32.994
And your dad made jokes
about my accent.

32:33.036 --> 32:37.123
[laughing]

32:37.165 --> 32:39.626
Andre taught me the difference
between good tequila

32:39.668 --> 32:43.505
and that gasoline Jesse Zeklos
smuggles into parties.

32:44.923 --> 32:49.219
Meanwhile, my mum was off
in parts unknown.

32:49.260 --> 32:52.347
And my dad, well, who knows?

32:54.057 --> 32:58.478
So the answer
to your question...

32:58.520 --> 33:00.939
if I'm okay,

33:00.980 --> 33:02.982
no.

33:03.024 --> 33:07.737
<i>* *</i>

33:07.779 --> 33:10.240
But I will be.

33:10.281 --> 33:13.618
And now,

33:13.660 --> 33:16.830
we get our own chance
to say goodbye,

33:16.871 --> 33:18.498
our own memorial.

33:18.540 --> 33:22.085
<i>- * I'm still a little broken,</i>
<i>but I'm healing *</i>

33:22.127 --> 33:26.214
<i>* Yeah, I'm still reeling *</i>

33:26.256 --> 33:30.051
<i>* I'm not okay *</i>

33:30.093 --> 33:32.470
- Be at peace.

33:32.512 --> 33:39.102
<i>* *</i>

33:41.938 --> 33:44.899
<i>[tense music]</i>

33:44.941 --> 33:52.115
<i>* *</i>

34:31.696 --> 34:33.198
- Thanks, Rose.

34:33.239 --> 34:35.492
I feel better
than I have in a while.

34:35.533 --> 34:37.243
- I know.

34:39.245 --> 34:42.665
I can kind of feel it
coming off of you.

34:44.334 --> 34:47.003
That's weird, right?

34:48.546 --> 34:50.799
- Not that weird.

34:50.840 --> 34:52.884
Feel like you've always been
pretty tuned into me.

34:52.926 --> 34:55.970
- Yeah.

34:56.012 --> 34:59.265
But this feels,

34:59.307 --> 35:02.727
I don't know, different somehow

35:02.769 --> 35:05.522
since you've been back.

35:09.484 --> 35:13.071
- Earlier, when you found me
in the garden,

35:13.113 --> 35:15.240
how did you know I was there?

35:15.281 --> 35:19.536
- I don't know, I just...did.

35:24.040 --> 35:27.085
[birds chirping]

35:27.127 --> 35:29.212
Oh, shit.

35:29.254 --> 35:31.965
Oh, we should get going.

35:32.007 --> 35:34.676
It's one thing to sneak outside
of the wards in the day,

35:34.718 --> 35:37.679
but if we get caught out here
during Strigoi hours,

35:37.721 --> 35:38.847
we're fucked.

35:38.888 --> 35:41.558
- Fine, but I'm driving.

35:43.226 --> 35:45.103
- You're stronger
than you look.

35:45.145 --> 35:46.187
- Just because
I'm not a Guard--

35:46.229 --> 35:49.190
[both grunt]

35:49.232 --> 35:51.693
Ow, shit.
- Are you okay?

35:51.735 --> 35:54.362
- Something's bruised.
Maybe my ego.

35:54.404 --> 35:56.156
- Can you walk?
- Yeah.

35:56.197 --> 35:58.783
<i>[tense music]</i>

35:58.825 --> 36:00.535
Oh, fuck.
I'm sorry, Rose.

36:00.577 --> 36:03.038
- Forget about walking.
We have to run.

36:03.079 --> 36:10.211
<i>* *</i>

36:12.922 --> 36:15.717
<i>- [growling]</i>
- [groans]

36:15.759 --> 36:16.843
- Rose, what's wrong?

36:16.885 --> 36:19.721
- I don't know. I feel sick.

36:19.763 --> 36:21.514
- [shrieking]

36:21.556 --> 36:25.643
- [screams]
- [growling]

36:27.145 --> 36:30.273
[roars]
- [screams]

36:30.315 --> 36:33.735
[both grunting]

36:36.780 --> 36:38.156
- Run!

36:40.950 --> 36:42.327
Go, Lissa!

36:42.369 --> 36:43.578
- I'm not just gonna
leave you here!

36:43.620 --> 36:45.747
- It's my job. Go!
- [screams]

36:45.789 --> 36:49.000
<i>* *</i>

36:49.042 --> 36:51.252
No, Rose!
- [roaring]

36:51.294 --> 36:53.254
- [groaning]

36:53.296 --> 36:56.257
- [growls]

36:56.299 --> 36:58.635
[shrieking]

37:05.809 --> 37:08.645
- [panting]

37:12.273 --> 37:13.692
I don't suppose there's any way

37:13.733 --> 37:15.318
we could keep this
just between us.

37:15.360 --> 37:18.488
[alarm blaring]

37:19.781 --> 37:22.951
[Guardians shouting]

37:22.992 --> 37:26.413
<i>* *</i>

37:33.086 --> 37:35.338
- That kind of risk
was unacceptable at any time.

37:35.380 --> 37:38.591
Now, the future
of the Dragomir family

37:38.633 --> 37:40.051
is in your hands.

37:40.093 --> 37:42.095
- A tiny family with no Andre

37:42.137 --> 37:44.097
in a society
with antiquated rules.

37:44.139 --> 37:45.348
What does it even matter?

37:45.390 --> 37:47.600
- If you think the rules
are antiquated now,

37:47.642 --> 37:49.477
wait till you see what happens
if any of the vipers

37:49.519 --> 37:51.396
jockeying for the crown
gets their way.

37:51.438 --> 37:53.940
Andre's rule
meant change for us.

37:53.982 --> 37:55.942
If the crown falls
to the wrong bloodline,

37:55.984 --> 37:58.111
whatever progress
your brother hoped to achieve

37:58.153 --> 38:00.280
will be impossible.

38:00.321 --> 38:02.240
The Dragomir vote is key
to preventing that.

38:02.282 --> 38:04.200
- Okay.

38:04.242 --> 38:07.454
I'll stay until
the succession is assured.

38:07.495 --> 38:10.999
Then I'll graduate
and get on with my life.

38:11.041 --> 38:12.375
Will that do?

38:15.503 --> 38:18.131
And please tell them
not to be too mad at Rose.

38:18.173 --> 38:21.343
- Lissa,
we are well beyond that.

38:23.011 --> 38:25.972
<i>[tense music]</i>

38:26.014 --> 38:32.896
<i>* *</i>

38:37.150 --> 38:38.943
- No need.

38:38.985 --> 38:41.946
I just got an earful
and then some from Alberta.

38:41.988 --> 38:44.783
Lissa and I aren't allowed
to be roommates anymore.

38:52.791 --> 38:54.417
I should have told you
I was taking Lissa

38:54.459 --> 38:56.378
outside of the wards.

38:56.419 --> 38:59.005
And I should have built in
more time on our return

38:59.047 --> 39:00.590
for unexpected complications.

39:00.632 --> 39:03.760
But I got her back
in one piece.

39:03.802 --> 39:06.680
I made sure she was protected.
They come first.

39:06.721 --> 39:10.016
- Protecting Lissa is my job.

39:10.058 --> 39:13.603
My only role here is to ensure
that nothing happens to her.

39:15.730 --> 39:18.191
What you did
was reckless and impulsive,

39:18.233 --> 39:21.027
no matter how good you are.

39:21.069 --> 39:25.073
Strength doesn't matter.
Style doesn't matter.

39:25.115 --> 39:27.158
Courage doesn't matter.

39:27.200 --> 39:30.245
There's good enough,
and there's gone.

39:32.497 --> 39:35.875
Tonight, you almost got
the person you say

39:35.917 --> 39:39.921
you care about most
in the world killed.

39:43.591 --> 39:45.218
There isn't a rank low enough
on that board

39:45.260 --> 39:46.594
for you right now.

39:48.513 --> 39:51.433
<i>[soft music]</i>

39:51.474 --> 39:55.270
<i>* *</i>

39:55.311 --> 39:57.063
- Hey, Rose.

39:57.105 --> 40:00.358
<i>* *</i>

40:00.400 --> 40:03.611
- Later, Rose.

40:03.653 --> 40:06.197
- Looks like you're slumming it
with the rest of us now.

40:06.239 --> 40:08.658
<i>- * Love it when you blossom,</i>
<i>shit is soft *</i>

40:08.700 --> 40:11.786
<i>* Naked as the truth</i>
<i>when you take it off *</i>

40:11.828 --> 40:14.664
<i>* I don't ever stoop,</i>
<i>stock is through the roof *</i>

40:14.706 --> 40:18.084
<i>* Graduating in a year,</i>
<i>leaving with the troops *</i>

40:18.126 --> 40:20.295
<i>* Man, this ain't no life</i>
<i>anyone can choose *</i>

40:20.337 --> 40:22.964
- You can have that bed
if you like.

40:23.006 --> 40:25.258
The view's nicer.

40:25.300 --> 40:29.346
<i>- * Whoa, yeah, we all souls *</i>

40:29.387 --> 40:32.599
<i>* Down the same road *</i>

40:32.640 --> 40:34.559
<i>* What scares you the most? *</i>

40:34.601 --> 40:37.354
<i>* Been down the longest road *</i>

40:37.395 --> 40:40.565
<i>* Oh, whoa *</i>

40:40.607 --> 40:43.485
<i>* Tell me what</i>
<i>scares you the most *</i>

40:43.526 --> 40:46.821
<i>* Whoa *</i>

40:46.863 --> 40:49.157
<i>* Tell me what</i>
<i>scares you the most *</i>

40:49.199 --> 40:53.119
<i>* Even when</i>
<i>your flesh gets cold *</i>

40:53.161 --> 40:54.704
<i>* You know who to call *</i>

40:54.746 --> 40:57.290
<i>- I wondered if you knew</i>
<i>how to say unicorn</i>

40:57.332 --> 40:59.084
<i>in Old Moroi.</i>

40:59.125 --> 41:02.796
<i>- * Not better off alone,</i>
<i>you're safe with me *</i>

41:02.837 --> 41:07.300
<i>* Don't change on me,</i>
<i>I can take you home *</i>

41:07.342 --> 41:10.053
<i>* You're safe with me,</i>
<i>don't change on me *</i>

41:10.095 --> 41:12.472
<i>* Don't change,</i>
<i>don't change, don't change *</i>

41:12.514 --> 41:15.350
<i>* Been a long road, whoa *</i>

41:15.392 --> 41:19.938
<i>* Yeah, we all souls,</i>
<i>down the same road *</i>

41:19.979 --> 41:23.566
<i>- I think unicorn in Moroi...</i>
<i>is Lissa.</i>

41:23.608 --> 41:26.194
<i>- * Been down</i>
<i>the longest road *</i>

41:26.236 --> 41:29.823
<i>* Oh, whoa *</i>

41:29.864 --> 41:32.367
<i>* Tell me what scares you</i>
<i>the most *</i>

41:32.409 --> 41:35.704
<i>* Oh, whoa *</i>

41:35.745 --> 41:38.373
<i>* Been down the longest road *</i>

41:38.415 --> 41:41.710
<i>* Oh, whoa *</i>

41:41.751 --> 41:44.379
<i>* Tell me</i>
<i>what scares you the most *</i>

41:44.421 --> 41:46.006
- Rose.

41:46.047 --> 41:50.218
- How come our mothers,
the same women who leave us

41:50.260 --> 41:52.929
on Academy doorsteps as infants

41:52.971 --> 41:55.932
so they can go back
to being Guardians,

41:55.974 --> 41:59.769
still get to tell us
what to do?

41:59.811 --> 42:01.521
- I wanted to see
if you're okay.

42:01.563 --> 42:03.440
- You didn't get
that many good shots in.

42:03.481 --> 42:05.191
I'll be fine.

42:05.233 --> 42:06.693
- I didn't mean that.

42:11.906 --> 42:16.953
- Mason, I really only have
two uses for you right now,

42:16.995 --> 42:21.458
and I'm not really
in the mood to spar, so...

42:29.299 --> 42:30.717
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

42:30.759 --> 42:32.802
Wait a minute, Rose.
Wait a minute.

42:32.844 --> 42:35.472
Hey.

42:35.513 --> 42:38.725
I can't believe
I'm actually saying this.

42:38.767 --> 42:42.687
I'm not here for that now
in this moment.

42:44.064 --> 42:46.566
I thought we could talk.

42:46.608 --> 42:49.069
Thought I could be a friend.

42:49.110 --> 42:50.445
- [laughs]

42:50.487 --> 42:52.906
- Just pretend I'm Lissa, okay?

42:52.947 --> 42:54.574
- [laughs]

42:54.616 --> 42:58.620
- Don't laugh.
What would she do now?

43:00.288 --> 43:03.416
- Today, it felt
like the universe

43:03.458 --> 43:06.711
was conspiring against me.

43:06.753 --> 43:09.422
I may have given it
some extra help,

43:09.464 --> 43:12.425
but all I wanted was

43:12.467 --> 43:15.387
to help my best friend
feel better,

43:15.428 --> 43:17.138
<i>and I did.</i>

43:17.180 --> 43:19.516
<i>but I also know</i>
<i>the only way for either of us</i>

43:19.557 --> 43:21.434
<i>to ever feel normal</i>
<i>or whole again</i>

43:21.476 --> 43:24.729
<i>is to leave this place</i>
<i>and go live our lives.</i>

43:24.771 --> 43:27.732
[phone ringing]

43:27.774 --> 43:30.443
<i>[tense music]</i>

43:30.485 --> 43:32.445
Hello.

43:32.487 --> 43:36.533
<i>* *</i>

43:36.574 --> 43:38.910
This is Rose.

43:38.952 --> 43:41.621
- It is a pleasure to meet you,
Novice Hathaway.

43:41.663 --> 43:43.581
- And you as well,
Your Majesty.

43:43.623 --> 43:45.500
- Vasilissa Dragomir

43:45.542 --> 43:48.503
is an important member
of this Dominion.

43:48.545 --> 43:51.214
I also know
she's important to you.

43:51.256 --> 43:53.842
- She is, Your Majesty.

43:53.883 --> 43:56.219
- Perhaps you can tell me why.

44:01.933 --> 44:06.479
- Guardians are raised
to be tough.

44:06.521 --> 44:09.941
It's the only way to survive,
especially as a woman.

44:11.651 --> 44:14.654
And I am tough.

44:14.696 --> 44:19.451
But I have seen what

44:19.492 --> 44:22.579
battle can do to people.

44:22.620 --> 44:27.500
Lissa keeps my heart

44:27.542 --> 44:29.669
in the right place.

44:29.711 --> 44:32.339
She always has a kind word

44:32.380 --> 44:35.842
or a compassionate ear
for anyone who needs it.

44:35.884 --> 44:40.055
She's everything good
and everything right.

44:40.096 --> 44:41.264
And she's...

44:41.306 --> 44:44.642
<i>[soft music]</i>

44:44.684 --> 44:46.644
She's my family.

44:46.686 --> 44:51.024
<i>* *</i>

44:51.066 --> 44:54.069
- Thank you, Novice Hathaway.

44:54.110 --> 44:56.154
You are excused.

44:57.447 --> 45:00.408
A toast to you all

45:00.450 --> 45:02.994
on St. Vladimir's Feast Day.

45:04.412 --> 45:07.248
The last I'll witnesses
as your sovereign.

45:07.290 --> 45:10.877
It is time to name the next.

45:10.919 --> 45:13.963
- Your Majesty,
protocol demands

45:14.005 --> 45:17.008
the announcement be made
in a more formal setting.

45:17.050 --> 45:21.471
- Protocol can kiss
my aging Royal buttocks.

45:21.513 --> 45:24.432
For the next heir
to the throne,

45:24.474 --> 45:27.811
I name Vasilissa Dragomir.

45:27.852 --> 45:30.814
[gasping, whispering]

45:30.855 --> 45:33.775
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

45:33.817 --> 45:40.949
<i>* *</i>

45:43.702 --> 45:45.704
- [breathing heavily]

46:18.737 --> 46:21.614
<i>[electronic orchestral music]</i>

46:21.656 --> 46:28.830
<i>* *</i>

47:13.708 --> 47:14.876
<i>[dog barks]</i>
